Quick reminder: the annual Clausen Center Faculty Debate is today, 4pm, in
Andersen Auditorium.

Topic: Currency Unions in the new Millenium: After Europe, are Asia and
Latin America next? Should they be?
Arguing in Favor: Andrew Rose
Arguing Against: Richard Lyons
Moderator: Janet Yellen
Sponsored by the Clausen Center for International Business and Policy.

A catered reception will follow the debate. We hope to see you there. Thanks.

